> | {{CSSRef}}
    ^
  | <p>The <strong><code>content</code></strong> <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</a> property replaces content with a generated value. It can be used to define what is rendered inside an element or pseudo-element. For elements, the <code>content</code> property specifies whether the element renders normally (<code>normal</code> or <code>none</code>) or is replaced with an image (and associated "alt" text). For pseudo-elements and margin boxes, <code>content</code> defines the content as images, text, both, or none, which determines whether the element renders at all.</p>
  | <p>Objects inserted using the <code>content</code> property are <strong>anonymous <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Replaced_element">replaced elements</a></strong>.</p>{{EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/tabbed/content.html", "tabbed-shorter")}}

